# WHAT IT IS
#   Chappe is the **GitBook-tier static documentation site
#   generator** for SaaS product teams — structurally positioned
#   as:
#
#     • **GitBook alternative** — without the SaaS dependency;
#       runs entirely as a `gulp build` + static-asset deploy
#     • **Docusaurus alternative** — but the audience is
#       SaaS product docs (not OSS project docs);  bundles a
#       separate API-reference sub-site (typical
#       Docusaurus + Redoc combination is two separate apps)
#     • **Mintlify alternative** — without the Mintlify SaaS
#       hosting tier;  bring-your-own-CDN
#     • **ReadMe.io alternative** — for teams that don't want
#       to send their unreleased API docs to a third-party
#       service
#     • **Slate / Bump.sh alternative** — but with Markdown +
#       multi-section navigation built-in (Slate is single-
#       page API reference;  Bump.sh is API-spec hosting)
#
#   Chappe's architecture: a `gulp build` pipeline reads
#   `data/<section>/<slug>.md` Markdown pages + `data/references/
#   *.yml` API reference entries + `config.json` global
#   configuration + `assets/` static assets, then renders nunjucks
#   templates with prismjs syntax highlighting + sharp image
#   optimization + sass-compiled styles, indexes the entire
#   content corpus with MiniSearch, and writes a static `dist/`
#   directory ready for any static-CDN deploy target (Netlify,
#   Vercel, Cloudflare Pages, S3+CloudFront, GitHub Pages).
#
#   Command-line surface (flat yargs CLI;  actions selected by
#   first positional arg, configuration injected by named flags):
#
#     Actions (one of):
#       build                         build the docs site to
#                                     `<dist>/`
#       clean                         clean `<dist>/` and the
#                                     `<temp>/` cache
#       watch                         build + watch source
#                                     directories for changes
#                                     (re-run on every change;
#                                     no-abort mode)
#       serve                         start the local dev HTTP
#                                     server with browser-sync
#                                     live-reload (no-abort)
#       lint                          run the docs lint pipeline
#                                     (link checker + Markdown
#                                     syntax + YAML reference
