# AXIS / CORPUS POSITION
#   `crisp-oss/chappe`'s `package.json` declares a **direct**
#   dependency on `minisearch@3.1.x`.  The
#   `gulp/tasks/search.js` task (the build-time index-emit step)
#   uses typed `MiniSearch.create({fields, storeFields,
#   searchOptions, idField})` to construct a typed index,
#   typed `index.addAll(documents)` to bulk-index every
#   Markdown page + API reference entry + changelog entry,
#   then typed `JSON.stringify(index)` to serialize the
#   MiniSearch state to `dist/<lang>/<section>/search-index.json`.
#   At runtime in the browser, the static site lazy-loads the
#   JSON via typed `MiniSearch.loadJSON(json, options)` and
#   handles user queries via typed `index.search(query, {
#   prefix, fuzzy, boost, weights, filter, combineWith })`.
#
#   **MiniSearch** (`minisearch` on npm) is **THE canonical
#   pure-JavaScript in-memory inverted-index library** —
#   Luca Ongaro's (lucaong on GitHub) reference pure-TypeScript
#   implementation of an inverted-index full-text search
#   engine, designed specifically for in-browser + edge-runtime
#   + serverless / embedded use cases where loading a Lucene-
#   equivalent native library is impossible.  In active
#   development since 2018, with 4,700+ ★ on github.com/
#   lucaong/minisearch.  Clocks 400,000+ weekly downloads on
#   npm.  The dominant pure-JS in-memory search library for
#   modern static-site-generator + Electron + browser-extension
#   + browser-SPA + Cloudflare Workers + Vercel Edge use
#   cases.
#
#   MiniSearch ships:
#
#     • Typed `MiniSearch.create({...})`
#       Typed `new MiniSearch({
#         fields, storeFields, idField,
#         extractField, tokenize, processTerm,
#         searchOptions, autoVacuum, autoSuggestOptions
#       })`                            typed constructor
#     • Typed `index.add(document)` /
#       `index.addAll(documents)` /
#       `index.addAllAsync(documents, options)`
#                                      typed index ingest
#     • Typed `index.remove(document)` /
#       `index.removeAll(documents)` /
#       `index.removeAllAsync()` /
#       `index.replace(newDoc)` /
#       `index.discard(id)` /
#       `index.discardAll(ids)`        typed mutation ops
#     • Typed `index.search(query, {
#         prefix, fuzzy, boost, weights,
#         combineWith, filter, processTerm,
#         tokenize, bm25,
#         searchOptions
#       })`                            typed search API with
#                                      typed `MiniSearchResult`
#                                      envelope: `{id, score,
#                                      terms, queryTerms, match,
#                                      ...storedFields}`
#     • Typed `index.autoSuggest(query, {prefix,
#         fuzzy, boost, weights, combineWith,
#         filter, processTerm, tokenize, bm25
#       })`                            typed autocomplete /
#                                      did-you-mean suggestions
#     • Typed `index.has(id)` /
#       `index.getStoredFields(id)`    typed lookups
#     • Typed `index.vacuum()` /
#       `index.isVacuuming` /
#       `index.conditionalVacuum()` /
#       `index.documentCount`          typed maintenance APIs
#     • Typed `index.toJSON()` /
#       Typed `MiniSearch.loadJSON(json, options)` /
#       Typed `MiniSearch.loadJSONAsync(json, options)`
#                                      typed serialize +
#                                      restore (the pattern
#                                      that enables build-time
#                                      indexing + runtime
#                                      lazy-load — the entire
#                                      reason chappe + every
#                                      Vitepress / Astro / Nuxt
#                                      docs site uses
#                                      MiniSearch)
#     • Typed `MiniSearch.wordCut` /
#       `MiniSearch.cjkTokenizer` /
#       custom typed `tokenize` /
#       `processTerm` hooks            typed multi-script
#                                      tokenization
#     • Typed BM25 scoring             configurable typed
#                                      `bm25: {k, b, d}`
#                                      parameters
#     • Typed prefix + fuzzy + phrase
#       queries                        typed `prefix: true |
#                                      false | fn`, typed
#                                      `fuzzy: 0..1`, typed
#                                      phrase quoting
#     • Typed boost per-field          typed `boost: {title: 2,
#                                      tags: 1.5, body: 1}`
#     • Typed combineWith              typed `combineWith:
#                                      "OR" | "AND" | "AND_NOT"`
#                                      operator selection
#     • Typed filter                   typed
#                                      `filter: (result) =>
#                                      result.category ===
#                                      "tutorial"` typed
#                                      callback
#     • Typed memory-efficient
#       posting lists                  bit-packed Roaring-
#                                      Bitmap-inspired
#                                      posting lists for
#                                      large index sizes
#     • Typed lazy index building
#       (`addAllAsync` with typed
#       `chunkSize` for browser-event-
#       loop yielding)
#     • Typed ESM + CJS dual-package
#       export
#     • Zero external dependencies     (the entire library is
#                                      <20KB minified+gzipped)
#
#   MiniSearch is the inverted-index library behind essentially
#   every modern pure-JS static-site documentation tool:
#
#     • **VitePress** (Vue's official Vite-powered static-site
#       generator;  18,800+ ★) — minisearch is the default
#       client-side local-search provider (`themeConfig.search:
#       { provider: "local" }`);  every Vue.js / Vite.js /
#       Vitest / Vitepress docs site uses MiniSearch
#     • **Nuxt Content** — the Nuxt 3 content-management
#       module;  minisearch under the @nuxt/content/search
#       sub-API
#     • **Astro Pagefind alternative** — for Astro sites that
#       want in-memory search instead of Pagefind's WebAssembly
#       approach
#     • **CASL** (the JavaScript isomorphic permissions library;
#       8,000+ ★) — minisearch in the docs site
#     • **Lowdefy** — the YAML web-app framework;  minisearch
#       for the docs portal
#     • **Robindoc** — TS-first documentation framework with
#       a dedicated minisearch integration package
#     • **Skiff** — the open-source end-to-end encrypted email
#       + drive + pages product
#     • **Crisp Chappe** (this very project)
#     • **MCP servers** (multiple: kontent-ai/mcp-server, mcp-
#       rtfm, Axiom/axiom-mcp, skydoves/android-skills-mcp,
#       fiedlermarius/sbox-mcp-documentation, etc.) — every
#       LLM-tool-context Markdown-knowledge-base MCP server
#       uses minisearch as the in-process search layer
#     • **Loreshelf** — Electron-based outliner with full-text
#       search
#     • **DDEV** — DDEV-Local docs site
#     • **Plus thousands of Astro / Eleventy / Hexo / Next.js
#       / Remix / SvelteKit / Qwik / SolidStart / Fresh /
#       Hono / Bun docs sites + browser-extensions + Tauri /
#       Electron / Capacitor apps with embedded search.
#
#   The MiniSearch project is structurally significant because
#   it enabled an entire class of applications: instant
#   in-browser search without a backend API.  Pre-MiniSearch,
#   the dominant pure-JS options were:
#     (a) **Lunr.js** (Oliver Nightingale, 2013) — predecessor
#         + ancestor;  excellent quality but lacks typed
#         autoSuggest, lacks incremental updates, lacks
#         streaming load, lacks fuzzy thresholds (0..1
#         interpolation), is more memory-heavy per indexed
#         token, and lacks ESM + tree-shaking;  Lunr is still
#         used heavily in Hugo / Jekyll / Eleventy / HonKit /
#         TypeDoc / Bitwarden / Moodle / Microsoft Fluid
#         Framework but is in maintenance-mode
#     (b) **Elasticlunr.js** — Lunr fork with extensions
#     (c) **FlexSearch** — non-Lucene-style architecture;
#         very fast but unconventional API
#     (d) **Fuse.js** — fuzzy-string scoring only (not a true
#         inverted-index);  good for typo-tolerant exact
#         matching, bad for multi-document corpus search
#   MiniSearch was the first pure-JS option that matched Lunr
#   feature-for-feature on the index + query path while adding
#   the typed JSON-round-trip semantics that enable build-time
#   indexing + runtime lazy-load — the architectural pattern
#   that powers every modern static-site search experience.
